"DISCOUNT IN TRADE It is a business custom, when a bill is paid before it is due, to allow a discount.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"This may be the legal rate of interest, or any percentage agreed on in advance.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"Sometimes wholesale merchants or manufacturers grant esteemed customers, in consideration of prompt payments, a discount from the regular prices.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"This is known as ""trade discount.""",0,0,0,0,0,0
We often read of two or more discounts.,0,0,0,0,0,0
A store keeper buys a bill of goods for $350 and is granted 20% and 5% from the selling price.,0,0,0,0,0,0
This does not mean a discount of 25% as the uninitiated might think.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"The 20% is deducted from the $350, that is, $70, leaving $280.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"Then the 5%, $14, is deducted from this, leaving $260.",0,0,0,0,0,0
Partial payments are not endorsed on the bill.,0,0,0,0,0,0
The receipt is written on a separate piece of paper.,0,0,0,0,0,0
