"A GOOD PLAN When you buy a draft which you mean to send off in payment of a debt, a good plan is to have it made payable to yourself.",1,0,0,0,0,0
Let us suppose it is the case of Albert Holt.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"You transfer the draft to him by writing across the back, ""Pay to the order of Albert Holt,"" and add your signature.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"Now as all drafts are returned, as payment vouchers, to the banks from which they were issued, and as Mr Holt must have signed the draft to get his money, it follows that there is a record of his having received it, and this has all the force of a receipt.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"Do not endorse a draft with just your name, for in that case, anyone into whose hands it falls may collect.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"First write ""Pay to the order of"" the person for whom it is intended.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"GOOD AS CASH A draft made payable to yourself is as good as cash, and far safer to carry.",0,0,0,0,0,0
